  "Metadata" -> {
   "built" -> "{2026, 4, 12, 17, 52, 52.844035}", 
    "history" -> {"14.1", "14.3", "", ""}, "context" -> "QuantumMob`Q3`", 
    "keywords" -> {
     "fermionic quantum computation", "fermionic Gaussian state"}, 
    "specialkeywords" -> {}, "tutorialcollectionlinks" -> {}, "index" -> True,
     "label" -> "Quantum Mob/ Q3 Symbol", "language" -> "en", "paclet" -> 
    "QuantumMob/Q3", "status" -> "None", "summary" -> 
    "BravyiMap[{..., speci, ...}] represents a fermionic Gaussian supermap \
\\[Rho] \\[RightTeeArrow] \\[CapitalSigma]i li ** \\[Rho] ** l_i^\\[Dagger] \
with each Gaussian element li ** \\[Rho] ** l_i^\\[Dagger] specified by \
speci. The specification speci of the form {ai, bi, di} -> fi means the \
action kernel of the block form {{ai, bi}, {- b_i^T, di}} and prefactor fi. \
The specification spec$i of the form {ai, bi} -> {sgni, fi} is equivalent to \
{ai, bi, sgni*ai} -> fi. BravyiMap[jmp] converts BravyiJump object jmp to the \
canonical form mentioned above. BravyiMap[msr] regards the measurement \
described by each row of BravyiMeasurement msr as a Kraus element, and \
converts BravyiMeasurement object msr to a BravyiMap object corresponding to \
\\[Rho] \\[RightTeeArrow] \\[CapitalSigma]i pi \\[Rho] pi, where pi is a \
projection operator pi := b_i^\\[Dagger] bi associated with dressed Dirac \
fermion mode bi specified in msr (see BravyiMeasurement for more about bi). \
With the option Completion -> True, each row v in msr are converted to v -> 4 \
(corresponding to the nonselective measurement \\[Rho] \\[RightTeeArrow] \
\\[CapitalSigma]i pi \\[Rho] pi + \\ \\[CapitalSigma]i (1 - pi ) \\[Rho] (1 - \
pi)); or v -> 2 otherwise.", "synonyms" -> {}, "tabletags" -> {}, "title" -> 
    "BravyiMap", "titlemodifier" -> "", "metadescription" -> "", 
    "windowtitle" -> "BravyiMap", "type" -> "Symbol", "uri" -> 
    "QuantumMob/Q3/ref/BravyiMap"}},
